===Noun===
'''[[mother-in-law]] [[apartment]]'''
#A small [[apartment]] attached to or carved out of a nominally single-family [[house]], ostensibly intended for occupancy by a [[mother-in-law]] or other relative, but potentially also [[rent]]ed out to a stranger.

===Citations===
*"Accessory dwelling units are commonly referred to as mother-in-law apartments.  Accessory dwelling units (ADUs) are a second dwelling on a piece of property where a primary residence already exists." —King County (Washington) [http://directory.metrokc.gov/ServiceDetail.asp?ServiceID=6955 Online Directory] <!-- fetched 2006-07-31 -->